Package BobcatLib.Utilities

Class CANDeviceDetails

java.lang.Object
BobcatLib.Utilities.CANDeviceDetails
public class CANDeviceDetails extends Object
This class represents the details of a CAN (Controller Area Network) device. It includes information such as the device's manufacturer, device number, bus, and subsystem name. This class is useful for managing and identifying CAN devices in a robotic system.

      public CANDeviceDetails(int deviceNumber, String bus, CANDeviceDetails.Manufacturer manufacturer, String subsystemName)
      Constructs a CANDeviceDetails object with the specified device number, bus name, manufacturer, and subsystem name.
      Parameters:
      deviceNumber - The unique identifier for the CAN device.
      bus - The bus name to which the device is connected.
      manufacturer - The manufacturer of the CAN device.
      subsystemName - The name of the subsystem this device is associated with.

    • CANDeviceDetails

      public CANDeviceDetails(int deviceNumber, String bus, CANDeviceDetails.Manufacturer manufacturer)
      Constructs a CANDeviceDetails object with the specified device number, bus name, and manufacturer. The subsystem name will be set to an empty string.
      Parameters:
      deviceNumber - The unique identifier for the CAN device.
      bus - The bus name to which the device is connected.
      manufacturer - The manufacturer of the CAN device.

    • CANDeviceDetails

      public CANDeviceDetails(int deviceNumber, CANDeviceDetails.Manufacturer manufacturer)
      Constructs a CANDeviceDetails object with the specified device number and manufacturer. The bus name will be set to an empty string, and the subsystem name will be set to an empty string.
      Parameters:
      deviceNumber - The unique identifier for the CAN device.
      manufacturer - The manufacturer of the CAN device.

    • CANDeviceDetails

      public CANDeviceDetails(int deviceNumber, CANDeviceDetails.Manufacturer manufacturer, String subsystemName)
      Constructs a CANDeviceDetails object with the specified device number, manufacturer, and subsystem name. The bus name will be set to an empty string.
      Parameters:
      deviceNumber - The unique identifier for the CAN device.
      manufacturer - The manufacturer of the CAN device.
      subsystemName - The name of the subsystem this device is associated with.

    • CANDeviceDetails

      public CANDeviceDetails(int deviceNumber)
      Constructs a CANDeviceDetails object with the specified device number. The bus name will be set to an empty string, and the manufacturer will be set to Unknown.
      Parameters:
      deviceNumber - The unique identifier for the CAN device.
